<statement>
<image width="33%" pi:generated="problems/images/mom-1057071-1.png"/><p>
Suppose a = 8 and c = 14. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20"/></p>
<p>
A = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20"/> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place. Give angles in <em>degrees</em>.
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>11.5</li><li>34.8</li><li>55.2</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{14}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{196}={64}+{b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{196}-{64}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{132}={b}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle\sqrt{{{132}}}={b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{11.489125293076}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{11.5}\approx{b}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle A</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arcsin{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{14}}\right)}}}\approx{34.849904579076}\approx{34.8}</m></p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\arccos{{\left(\frac{{8}}{{14}}\right)}}}\approx{55.150095420924}\approx{55.2}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>